# Per-developer overrides for `npm run test:e2e` and `npm run coverage`.
# Copy to `.env` (gitignored) and tweak for your local LLM server.
#
# Both vars are optional — defaults live in tests/e2e/helpers/harness.mjs:
#   AUTOREVIEW_E2E_ENDPOINT=http://127.0.0.1:8080/v1
#   AUTOREVIEW_E2E_MODEL=unsloth/Qwen3.6-35B-A3B-UD-MLX-4bit
#
# E2E suites guard each test with `serverAvailable()` and skip when the
# endpoint is unreachable, so the test run still passes on machines with
# no local LLM.

# Example: host-side llama-server on port 8089 with the GGUF Q4_K_M weights.
AUTOREVIEW_E2E_ENDPOINT=http://127.0.0.1:8089/v1
AUTOREVIEW_E2E_MODEL=Qwen3.6-35B-A3B-UD-Q4_K_M.gguf
